WEBVTT

1
00:00:50.133 --> 00:00:54.219
...what has
turned into a classic Formula 1 season.

2
00:00:55.889 --> 00:00:57.848
With the
weather conditions so uncertain.

3
00:00:57.974 --> 00:00:59.141
the drivers prepare for...

4
00:01:01.811 --> 00:01:03.812
...the track is still dangepously wet.

5
00:01:03.855 --> 00:01:05.230
but following a drivers' meeting.

6
00:01:05.315 --> 00:01:08.400
- a decision has finally been taken.
- Three minutes to go.

7
00:01:09.069 --> 00:01:11.153
Everybody off the grid now.

8
00:01:25.168 --> 00:01:29.254
Twenty-five drivers
start every season in Formula 1.

9
00:01:29.339 --> 00:01:32.382
and each year two of us die.

10
00:01:33.176 --> 00:01:35.511
What kind of person
does a job like this?

11
00:01:36.679 --> 00:01:38.680
Not normal men. for sure.

12
00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:43.018
Rebels. lunatics. dreamers.

13
00:01:43.686 --> 00:01:46.063
People who are desperate to make a mark

14
00:01:46.189 --> 00:01:48.440
and are prepared to die trying.

15
00:01:50.527 --> 00:01:51.860
My name is Niki Lauda.

16
00:01:52.237 --> 00:01:55.364
and racing people
know me for two things.

17
00:01:55.448 --> 00:01:59.201
The first is my rivalry with him.

18
00:02:03.373 --> 00:02:06.291
Photographers.
please clear the grid.

19
00:02:06.793 --> 00:02:08.752
What about Hunt? Has he changed?

20
00:02:09.045 --> 00:02:10.462
No. he's going on wets.

21
00:02:10.547 --> 00:02:13.715
I don't know
why it became such a big thing.

22
00:02:13.758 --> 00:02:17.136
We were just drivers
busting each other's balls.

23
00:02:18.138 --> 00:02:20.556
To me this is perfectly normal.

24
00:02:20.640 --> 00:02:22.808
but other people saw it differently.

25
00:02:22.892 --> 00:02:25.811
that whatever it was between us
went deeper.

26
00:02:42.078 --> 00:02:44.079
The other thing I'm remembered for

27
00:02:44.164 --> 00:02:47.916
is what happened on 1st August. 1976.

28
00:02:48.001 --> 00:02:49.501
when I was chasing him

29
00:02:49.586 --> 00:02:51.670
like an asshole.

30
00:03:22.202 --> 00:03:23.619
Trauma trolley. please.

31
00:03:23.703 --> 00:03:26.121
Hello. I think the racetrack
telephoned ahead that I was coming.

32
00:03:26.206 --> 00:03:27.623
Hunt. James Hunt.

33
00:03:32.712 --> 00:03:35.797
What's the matter? No one ever seen
a spot of blood before?

34
00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:38.800
- Are you all right?
- Absolutely fine.

35
00:03:41.971 --> 00:03:43.847
We all thought
you'd been in an accident.

36
00:03:43.973 --> 00:03:45.015
I have.

37
00:03:45.141 --> 00:03:48.310
If you call a friendly disagreement
with another driver an accident.

38
00:03:54.484 --> 00:03:56.235
What did you disagree about?

39
00:03:56.319 --> 00:03:57.861
It's none of your business.

40
00:03:57.987 --> 00:03:59.988
...Sorry.

41
00:04:00.990 --> 00:04:02.366
His wife.

42
00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:06.912
That's going to need a couple
of stitches. It's a nasty cut.

43
00:04:06.996 --> 00:04:10.082
It was a nasty blow.
Done with a bloody crowbar.

44
00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:13.752
- Why? What did you do?
- Nothing.

45
00:04:14.379 --> 00:04:16.588
Only what she asked me to do.

46
00:04:18.841 --> 00:04:20.342
Which was...

47
00:04:21.010 --> 00:04:23.512
I'd be happy to show you. if you like.

48
00:04:26.724 --> 00:04:29.017
...Oh! Sorry.

49
00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:32.938
I have a theory
why women like racing drivers.

50
00:04:33.273 --> 00:04:35.607
It's not because
they respect what we do.

51
00:04:35.692 --> 00:04:38.485
driving pound and pound in circles.

52
00:04:38.569 --> 00:04:41.113
Mostly they think that's pathetic.
and they're ppobably right.

53
00:04:42.365 --> 00:04:44.449
It's our closeness to death.

54
00:04:45.285 --> 00:04:48.954
You see. the closer you are to death.
the more alive you feel.

55
00:04:49.038 --> 00:04:52.040
The more alive you are.
And they can see that in you.

56
00:04:52.125 --> 00:04:54.042
They feel that in you.

57
00:04:55.211 --> 00:04:57.421
My name is James Hunt.

58
00:04:57.547 --> 00:04:59.548
My father is a stockbpoker.

59
00:04:59.590 --> 00:05:03.218
my sister is a barrister
and my bpother is an accountant.

60
00:05:04.262 --> 00:05:05.721
And I...

61
00:05:06.222 --> 00:05:07.889
Well. I do this.

62
00:05:09.392 --> 00:05:10.934
It's a wonderful way to live.

63
00:05:11.060 --> 00:05:13.103
It's the only way to drive.

64
00:05:14.063 --> 00:05:16.481
As if each day is your last.

65
00:05:25.742 --> 00:05:28.243
I've never been to a Grand Prix before.

66
00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:30.162
Oh. you still haven't.

67
00:05:30.246 --> 00:05:32.748
- This is Formula 3.
- What's that?

68
00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:35.834
It's a lower division.

69
00:05:35.918 --> 00:05:38.420
where idiots like me mess about

70
00:05:38.838 --> 00:05:41.506
in the hope of being talent-spotted
to race in Formula 1.

71
00:05:41.591 --> 00:05:43.592
- You look disappointed.
- No.

72
00:05:44.093 --> 00:05:47.262
Ah. You only slept with me
because you thought I was famous.

73
00:05:47.347 --> 00:05:48.930
That's not true.

74
00:05:49.599 --> 00:05:51.600
Don't worry. I will be one day.

75
00:05:51.684 --> 00:05:53.268
Morning. everyone.

76
00:05:53.311 --> 00:05:54.936
- This is Nursie.
- Gemma.

77
00:05:55.605 --> 00:05:58.440
Nursie. this is Bubbles Horsley.
team manager.

78
00:05:58.524 --> 00:05:59.608
How do you do?

79
00:05:59.984 --> 00:06:01.777
- Bubbles?
- Yeah.

80
00:06:01.819 --> 00:06:04.780
- Doc Postlethwaite. our designer.
- How do you do?

81
00:06:04.864 --> 00:06:08.784
And Alexander. Lord Hesketh.
the team's owner.

82
00:06:09.827 --> 00:06:11.328
How do you do?

83
00:06:12.163 --> 00:06:13.622
Fine. thanks.

84
00:06:13.664 --> 00:06:15.540
Well done. Superstar.

85
00:06:15.625 --> 00:06:18.168
- That's the car?
- Yep. that's her.

86
00:06:18.294 --> 00:06:20.003
Lotus 59.

87
00:06:20.129 --> 00:06:22.839
1.000cc Cosworth MAE engine.

88
00:06:22.965 --> 00:06:25.801
She's no beauty.
but goes like the clappers.

89
00:06:32.350 --> 00:06:34.393
Nothing to be worried about.
Does it before every race.

90
00:06:34.477 --> 00:06:36.561
Good sign. actually. Means he's stoked.

91
00:06:36.646 --> 00:06:40.857
All Formula 3 cars
to the assembly area now. please.

92
00:06:52.578 --> 00:06:55.747
...drivers please bring them
to the scrutineering bay now.

93
00:06:56.165 --> 00:06:57.707
All right. Superstar?

94
00:06:57.834 --> 00:06:59.501
Never better. patron.

95
00:06:59.544 --> 00:07:02.045
- Have a gargle with this.
- Thank you.

96
00:07:03.506 --> 00:07:04.923
Quick toke of this.

97
00:07:05.842 --> 00:07:08.718
At Crystal Palace today.
James Hunt's on pole.

98
00:07:09.554 --> 00:07:12.848
with Austrian newcomer
Niki Lauda alongside him

99
00:07:12.890 --> 00:07:15.517
and Dave Walker completing Row 1.

100
00:07:15.601 --> 00:07:18.061
Row 2 is Mike Beuttler and Dave Morgan.

101
00:07:18.187 --> 00:07:21.064
- with Tony Trimmer and Gerry Birrell.
- Who's that?

102
00:07:21.441 --> 00:07:22.941
He's new.

103
00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:26.278
- Some German.
- Austrian.

104
00:07:26.362 --> 00:07:29.448
He's been here since 5:00 am.
walking the track.

105
00:07:29.532 --> 00:07:31.867
You might actually
have to concentrate today. James.

106
00:07:31.951 --> 00:07:33.577
You'll need these.

107
00:07:34.245 --> 00:07:36.788
Okay. start her up.

108
00:07:36.873 --> 00:07:39.374
Ah! What music!

109
00:07:39.417 --> 00:07:40.876
They could never have imagined it.

110
00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:43.253
those pioneers
who invented the automobile.

111
00:07:43.379 --> 00:07:47.549
that it would possess us like this.
in our imaginations. in our dreams.

112
00:07:48.301 --> 00:07:50.594
Nursie. men love women.

113
00:07:50.720 --> 00:07:52.471
but even more than that.

114
00:07:52.555 --> 00:07:55.891
men love cars.

115
00:08:02.982 --> 00:08:06.151
- Come on. James!
- James! Come on. James!

116
00:08:07.153 --> 00:08:08.570
Go. James!

117
00:08:16.245 --> 00:08:17.412
Hunt's still in the lead.

118
00:08:17.497 --> 00:08:19.623
but Niki Lauda is right on his tail.

119
00:08:28.424 --> 00:08:31.259
Hunt and Lauda are
ppoving to be in a class of their own.

120
00:08:31.302 --> 00:08:32.928
They're leaving the pack far behind.

121
00:08:33.304 --> 00:08:34.930
Herr Red Devil's on his tail.

122
00:08:41.020 --> 00:08:43.021
Lauda takes a look down the inside...

123
00:08:44.690 --> 00:08:46.441
...and he's sold him a dummy!

124
00:08:49.946 --> 00:08:51.947
Lauda is thpough! He's in the lead!

125
00:08:52.782 --> 00:08:55.200
Hunt will be determined
to make up for that mistake.

126
00:09:01.958 --> 00:09:03.500
Hunt's in Lauda's slipstream.

127
00:09:03.626 --> 00:09:05.585
Lauda's not leaving any gap.

128
00:09:10.716 --> 00:09:14.719
The Lotus goes for the inside.
It's an aggressive move fpom Hunt.

129
00:09:18.808 --> 00:09:20.725
Oh! There's contact!

130
00:09:27.483 --> 00:09:30.735
The leaders have spun out!
Lauda's facing the wpong way!

131
00:09:31.320 --> 00:09:33.697
The back marker's gone thpough.

132
00:09:34.031 --> 00:09:35.657
...You can see why Hunt's fellow drivers

133
00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:37.534
call him "Hunt the Shunt".

134
00:09:40.997 --> 00:09:41.997
Asshole!

135
00:09:42.081 --> 00:09:43.832
- Go on. James!
- The Kraut's out of it.

136
00:09:44.166 --> 00:09:46.084
Lauda is clearly furious.

137
00:09:46.168 --> 00:09:49.588
There's every reason
to expect sharp words in the pits.

138
00:09:49.672 --> 00:09:51.548
It's gonna be victory for Hunt.

139
00:09:51.674 --> 00:09:55.010
It's gonna be an ignominious defeat
for Niki Lauda.

140
00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:03.602
So James Hunt scores his
third major Formula 3 win of the season

141
00:10:03.686 --> 00:10:04.936
here at Crystal Palace.

142
00:10:05.021 --> 00:10:07.772
after a desperate battle
with Niki Lauda.

143
00:10:07.857 --> 00:10:09.566
Lauda was unable to restart

144
00:10:09.692 --> 00:10:12.402
after Hunt's aggressive move
caused them both to spin out

145
00:10:12.528 --> 00:10:13.695
in the last lap of the race.

146
00:10:15.114 --> 00:10:16.698
Hard luck.
Better luck next time.

147
00:10:17.366 --> 00:10:18.867
Hey. asshole.

148
00:10:19.952 --> 00:10:22.120
That was my line. I had that corner.

149
00:10:22.204 --> 00:10:25.457
Do you mean the one that you spun out of
and finished facing the other way?

150
00:10:25.541 --> 00:10:27.876
I think that corner had you.

151
00:10:27.960 --> 00:10:30.462
That move was total suicide.
What if I hadn't braked?

152
00:10:30.546 --> 00:10:33.381
- We'd have crashed.
- But we didn't. did we?

153
00:10:33.424 --> 00:10:35.383
Thanks to your impeccable
survival instincts.

154
00:10:37.553 --> 00:10:39.387
Fuck you. What's your name?

155
00:10:41.057 --> 00:10:45.393
James Simon Wallis Hunt.
Remember it. my little Jerry friend.

156
00:10:45.770 --> 00:10:47.395
Jawohl. Remember ze name.

157
00:10:47.438 --> 00:10:50.231
And it's very simple. Hunt.
It rhymes with...

158
00:10:50.274 --> 00:10:51.399
...cunt.

159
00:10:51.484 --> 00:10:53.943
A word that happens
to describe you perfectly!

160
00:10:54.570 --> 00:10:55.987
Who was that?

161
00:10:56.072 --> 00:10:58.239
I've no idea.
He looks like a rat. doesn't he?

162
00:11:00.576 --> 00:11:01.993
In my home town. Vienna.

163
00:11:02.453 --> 00:11:05.747
my family is famous
for one thing - business.

164
00:11:06.332 --> 00:11:08.583
My grandfather was a businessman.

165
00:11:09.085 --> 00:11:10.502
my father. too.

166
00:11:11.337 --> 00:11:14.422
So when they heard I wanted
to race cars for a living.

167
00:11:14.507 --> 00:11:16.299
they had a few things to say.

168
00:11:41.450 --> 00:11:42.784
Gut.

169
00:12:03.472 --> 00:12:05.473
So if my family
wasn't going to help me.

170
00:12:05.641 --> 00:12:09.310
I decided to risk everything
and take out a loan myself.

171
00:12:09.395 --> 00:12:12.355
I found a Formula 1 team
with an okay car

172
00:12:12.481 --> 00:12:14.524
and an owner who had run out of money

173
00:12:14.650 --> 00:12:16.818
and was willing to accept my terms.

174
00:12:17.194 --> 00:12:18.862
And so.
ladies and gentlemen.

175
00:12:18.988 --> 00:12:20.739
I'm delighted to say

176
00:12:20.823 --> 00:12:24.367
that the winner of the Guild of Motoring
Writers Award Driver of the Year...

177
00:12:25.578 --> 00:12:26.578
is James Hunt.

178
00:12:30.499 --> 00:12:31.916
Superb news!

179
00:12:32.668 --> 00:12:34.836
- Well done. James.
- Superstar!

180
00:12:35.004 --> 00:12:36.421
Fantastic!

181
00:12:38.007 --> 00:12:40.216
- Well done. Congratulations.
- Thank you so much.

182
00:12:40.342 --> 00:12:41.426
Yes!

183
00:12:41.510 --> 00:12:42.844
Erm...

184
00:12:42.887 --> 00:12:45.680
You know. my parents
always wanted me to be a doctor...

185
00:12:45.848 --> 00:12:47.891
...or a stockbroker or something.

186
00:12:48.017 --> 00:12:49.684
They gave me the first-class education.

187
00:12:49.769 --> 00:12:51.853
but. well. that all went terribly wrong

188
00:12:51.937 --> 00:12:53.688
and I ended up with you lot.

189
00:12:56.776 --> 00:12:58.234
Thank you. I need it more than you do.

190
00:13:00.404 --> 00:13:04.073
I mean. I have a hot head.
an inability to tolerate discipline.

191
00:13:04.200 --> 00:13:05.575
- Yes!
- Very true.

192
00:13:06.285 --> 00:13:08.119
I fall out with people left and right.

193
00:13:08.746 --> 00:13:11.790
The only creatures I've ever really
loved or have treated honourably

194
00:13:11.874 --> 00:13:13.875
are budgerigars.

195
00:13:15.211 --> 00:13:19.214
So in any normal area of life I'd be...
or I am. a total liability.

196
00:13:19.548 --> 00:13:21.758
The only thing I've got going for me
is I'm quick in a car.

197
00:13:22.051 --> 00:13:23.968
So. thank you for this
and for acknowledging that.

198
00:13:24.053 --> 00:13:25.470
I'm going to give it to my father

199
00:13:25.554 --> 00:13:27.305
and tell him to put it
on the mantelpiece

200
00:13:27.389 --> 00:13:29.724
and imagine it's a first-class degree
in medicine.

201
00:13:45.074 --> 00:13:46.908
Well done. Superstar.

202
00:13:46.951 --> 00:13:49.577
Another season like that
and I'll move you up to the big time.

203
00:13:49.662 --> 00:13:51.246
Come on. you don't think I'm ready now?

204
00:13:51.330 --> 00:13:54.666
You are. I'm not.
I've got to find you a car first.

205
00:13:54.834 --> 00:13:57.168
Well. go on. then. Chop-chop.

206
00:13:57.253 --> 00:13:59.504
Don't wait too long. You don't want him
to do what Lauda just did.

207
00:13:59.588 --> 00:14:02.590
- Why? What did he do?
- Got himself a drive with BRM.

208
00:14:02.633 --> 00:14:04.843
Well. how the hell did he do that?
He's a nobody.

209
00:14:04.927 --> 00:14:06.344
He's never won a bloody thing.

210
00:14:06.428 --> 00:14:08.346
Apparently. took out a loan
and bought his way in

211
00:14:08.430 --> 00:14:10.098
with two million Austrian schillings.

212
00:14:10.140 --> 00:14:11.599
Jesus.

213
00:14:31.120 --> 00:14:34.163
Niki Lauda.
Here for pre-season testing. BRM?

214
00:14:35.666 --> 00:14:38.459
Sign the release form.
I'll let them know you're here.

215
00:14:50.222 --> 00:14:51.764
- Mr Stanley.
- Good morning.

216
00:14:51.807 --> 00:14:54.726
- Good morning.
- Good morning. Clay!

217
00:14:54.810 --> 00:14:57.478
Let me introduce you
to our number-one driver.

218
00:14:57.563 --> 00:14:59.564
Clay Regazzoni.

219
00:15:00.941 --> 00:15:02.692
- How are you?
- Good.

220
00:15:03.444 --> 00:15:06.446
- Pleasure.
- And these are your mechanics.

221
00:15:06.989 --> 00:15:11.451
They're reporting exclusively to you.
as per contract.

222
00:15:11.535 --> 00:15:13.286
Pleasure. Do you wanna see the car?

223
00:15:13.370 --> 00:15:14.787
Sure.

224
00:15:16.832 --> 00:15:18.249
Hello.

225
00:15:23.297 --> 00:15:25.715
There she is. P160.

226
00:15:26.592 --> 00:15:29.135
- Same as Regazzoni's?
- Identical in every detail.

227
00:15:30.095 --> 00:15:31.554
How much does she weigh?

228
00:15:31.722 --> 00:15:34.307
- 600 kilos.
- But that's crazy.

229
00:15:34.516 --> 00:15:37.101
- Why so heavy?
- It's a V12 engine.

230
00:15:37.186 --> 00:15:40.313
That lump weighs 190K on its own.

231
00:15:40.397 --> 00:15:42.315
Okay.

232
00:15:42.399 --> 00:15:44.692
What horsepower are you getting? 490?

233
00:15:44.777 --> 00:15:47.153
- No. no. 450.
- Well. it's not enough.

234
00:15:47.237 --> 00:15:48.655
It needs to be 500.

235
00:15:48.739 --> 00:15:50.406
and the engine
needs to be 20 kilo lighter.

236
00:15:50.491 --> 00:15:51.699
We already tried.

237
00:15:51.784 --> 00:15:52.951
- Tried what?
- Evertyhing.

238
00:15:53.160 --> 00:15:54.619
We replaced the entire exhaust system.

239
00:15:54.703 --> 00:15:57.997
- Barely made a difference.
- Are you using magnesium parts?

240
00:16:11.053 --> 00:16:12.470
Now the engine block.

241
00:16:12.554 --> 00:16:15.264
Any mounting or fixing plates.
strip it out also.

242
00:16:15.599 --> 00:16:18.685
When you've done that.
we have to look at the aerodynamics.

243
00:16:18.769 --> 00:16:20.520
front and rear wing.

244
00:16:37.955 --> 00:16:40.039
Okay. thank you. Good night.

245
00:17:00.019 --> 00:17:01.436
What was Regazzoni's time?

246
00:17:03.313 --> 00:17:04.731
1:53.

247
00:17:05.065 --> 00:17:07.900
Okay. now put him in my car.
and he'll go round two seconds faster.

248
00:17:07.985 --> 00:17:11.029
- Well. that's impossible.
- No chance.

249
00:17:14.074 --> 00:17:16.367
We've been working on it all night.

250
00:17:16.452 --> 00:17:18.494
Put Regazzoni in the car.
See what happens.

251
00:17:18.579 --> 00:17:20.413
I don't understand.
Why am I supposed to do this?

252
00:17:20.497 --> 00:17:22.415
I don't know. Clay.
He just wants you to take it for a spin.

253
00:17:25.669 --> 00:17:27.211
Gloves. please.

254
00:17:27.296 --> 00:17:28.713
'Fanculo.

255
00:18:11.924 --> 00:18:14.967
- I would say we push it a bit...
- All right.

256
00:18:15.052 --> 00:18:17.053
What did you do to the car?

257
00:18:17.137 --> 00:18:20.640
That's information I will share with you
under certain conditions only.

258
00:18:20.891 --> 00:18:22.308
Go on.

259
00:18:23.393 --> 00:18:25.061
A guaranteed place in the team.

260
00:18:25.437 --> 00:18:27.814
and a paid contract on equal terms
with Regazzoni for two years.

261
00:18:29.191 --> 00:18:30.817
Are you crazy?

262
00:18:30.901 --> 00:18:34.445
Clay's a senior figure in Formula 1.
You're just a rookie.

263
00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:36.948
Well. the only reason we took you on
is because you're paying us.

264
00:18:37.658 --> 00:18:40.868
Well. as of now. if you want me to stay.
we rip up the contract.

265
00:18:40.953 --> 00:18:43.663
- I don't pay you a cent.
- That's outrageous!

266
00:18:44.206 --> 00:18:46.290
Was he quicker in my car?

267
00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:49.001
He was. wasn't he?

268
00:18:49.711 --> 00:18:51.963
Did he go two seconds faster?

269
00:18:55.592 --> 00:18:57.051
2.3.

270
00:18:59.763 --> 00:19:01.889
So. have a think.

271
00:19:02.516 --> 00:19:04.767
work out your priorities
and get back to me.

272
00:19:19.741 --> 00:19:21.159
Hey. Niki.

273
00:19:23.579 --> 00:19:26.455
I know what you're going to say.
that it's none of my business.

274
00:19:26.540 --> 00:19:27.540
What?

275
00:19:28.959 --> 00:19:32.295
If it's the track manager
you're taking on your date tonight...

276
00:19:33.338 --> 00:19:34.881
it's none of your business.

277
00:19:34.965 --> 00:19:38.718
Okay. but if you want my advice.
I'd let this one go.

278
00:19:40.095 --> 00:19:43.723
I'm not questioning your taste.
She is a great girl. but...

279
00:19:45.350 --> 00:19:49.228
Agnes's last boyfriend
was a British Formula 2 driver

280
00:19:49.313 --> 00:19:51.647
who has a reputation for two things.

281
00:19:51.732 --> 00:19:54.400
For being a little crazy on the track.

282
00:19:54.568 --> 00:19:58.738
and for going all night and all day
and all night again in bed.

283
00:19:58.822 --> 00:20:02.283
He's a good driver.
but an immortal fuck. apparently.

284
00:20:02.367 --> 00:20:05.328
I don't know about you. but
that's not an act I'd like to follow.

285
00:20:08.624 --> 00:20:10.708
But if that doesn't bother you...

286
00:20:12.628 --> 00:20:15.588
What's his name. the driver?

287
00:20:15.839 --> 00:20:17.340
Hunt. James Hunt.

288
00:20:21.470 --> 00:20:24.931
You see. you share information
and I share information.

289
00:20:26.266 --> 00:20:28.476
That's what teammates are for.

290
00:20:38.737 --> 00:20:40.196
Where the hell are we going?

291
00:20:40.280 --> 00:20:42.573
I ppomise
it'll be worth it.

292
00:20:42.658 --> 00:20:44.075
Just keep them closed.

293
00:20:44.534 --> 00:20:45.952
Wait for it.

294
00:20:46.787 --> 00:20:48.579
Wait for it.

295
00:20:51.959 --> 00:20:54.418
There. What do you say?

296
00:20:54.503 --> 00:20:56.087
She's Formula 1.

297
00:20:56.505 --> 00:20:58.214
Yes. she is. Superstar.

298
00:20:58.632 --> 00:21:01.425
Your brother and I got together
with the bean counters.

299
00:21:01.510 --> 00:21:02.927
And since the economics of F1

300
00:21:03.011 --> 00:21:06.555
are not so significantly different
to the economics of Formula 2.

301
00:21:06.640 --> 00:21:09.058
well. we thought if we were
going to be losing money.

302
00:21:09.142 --> 00:21:12.186
we might as well be doing it on
the big roulette table in Formula 1.

303
00:21:12.271 --> 00:21:15.606
You fat. little. inbred beauty.
Come here.

304
00:21:19.903 --> 00:21:23.239
Actually. credit where it's due.
we got the idea from Niki.

305
00:21:23.532 --> 00:21:25.449
- Who?
- Lauda.

306
00:21:25.534 --> 00:21:28.286
Bought his way in. rather than
mess about in the lower divisions.

307
00:21:28.370 --> 00:21:29.912
I thought. "Bloody hell. he's right."

308
00:21:30.163 --> 00:21:33.541
No sponsorship. Superstar.
I hope you approve.

309
00:21:33.625 --> 00:21:37.628
No vulgar logos
for cigarettes or condoms.

310
00:21:38.213 --> 00:21:40.256
Just plain white with the flags. Ooh!

311
00:21:40.674 --> 00:21:43.634
And racing overalls which read.

312
00:21:44.845 --> 00:21:47.346
"Sex. Breakfast of champions."

313
00:21:50.100 --> 00:21:51.934
So. when do we start?

314
00:21:52.894 --> 00:21:55.062
- Soon as you're ready.
- Ready?

315
00:21:55.397 --> 00:21:57.940
I've been waiting for this
my whole life.

316
00:22:06.950 --> 00:22:08.909
- Hi. welcome to Watkins Glen.
- Hello!

317
00:22:08.994 --> 00:22:10.745
When the season started.
people wondered

318
00:22:11.079 --> 00:22:13.873
whether Lord Hesketh and his team
of upper-class enthusiasts

319
00:22:14.249 --> 00:22:18.627
were bringing glamour
to the racing community. or just comedy.

320
00:22:18.712 --> 00:22:20.796
Certainly. it was the first time
anyone had seen

321
00:22:20.881 --> 00:22:24.425
a butler serving oysters and caviar
in the pits.

322
00:22:24.509 --> 00:22:27.261
But they have made quite an impact.

323
00:22:27.346 --> 00:22:30.514
Sixth in France. fourth in Britain
and third in Holland.

324
00:22:30.599 --> 00:22:34.185
All drivers on the track.
caution flags are out.

325
00:22:34.269 --> 00:22:36.354
A severe crash at the Esses.

326
00:22:36.688 --> 00:22:38.481
Red flag.
There is a car off the track.

327
00:22:38.565 --> 00:22:40.232
And reports are reaching me

328
00:22:40.317 --> 00:22:42.526
that there has been
a serious accident in qualifying.

329
00:22:42.861 --> 00:22:45.404
Er. the identity of the driver we don't
currently have at the moment.

330
00:22:45.489 --> 00:22:47.698
but. as you can tell
from all the activity

331
00:22:47.783 --> 00:22:49.408
going on behind me towards the track.

332
00:22:49.493 --> 00:22:51.869
it is clearly a grave incident indeed.

333
00:22:51.953 --> 00:22:53.371
We will. of course.
have more information for you

334
00:22:53.455 --> 00:22:54.497
as and when we get it.

335
00:22:54.581 --> 00:22:58.584
but it is the sight and sound
of Formula 1 nobody likes to see.

336
00:23:02.589 --> 00:23:04.340
- Get your hands off me.
- Hey. come on.

337
00:23:14.518 --> 00:23:15.893
Drivers of top stature

338
00:23:15.977 --> 00:23:17.686
we've lost just in the past four seasons

339
00:23:17.771 --> 00:23:22.608
have included Piers Courage.
Jochen Rindt.

340
00:23:22.692 --> 00:23:25.945
Jo Siffert. Roger Williamson

341
00:23:26.029 --> 00:23:28.239
and today. at Watkins Glen.

342
00:23:28.323 --> 00:23:30.658
Formula 1 has claimed another driver.

343
00:23:31.243 --> 00:23:33.536
The Tyrrell team
have withdrawn fpom the race.

344
00:23:33.620 --> 00:23:36.288
Their places on the grid
will be left empty.

345
00:23:36.373 --> 00:23:38.791
- Terrible.
- They should cancel the race.

346
00:23:39.042 --> 00:23:40.543
Why?

347
00:23:40.877 --> 00:23:43.337
He made a mistake.
went into the corner too fast.

348
00:23:43.422 --> 00:23:44.839
It's his fault.

349
00:23:44.923 --> 00:23:46.799
- Is that right?
- It's obvious.

350
00:23:47.217 --> 00:23:48.926
Look at the tyre marks.

351
00:23:49.302 --> 00:23:52.555
So says the nobody
who had to pay for his own drive.

352
00:23:52.639 --> 00:23:54.056
How's that working out for you.
by the way?

353
00:23:54.516 --> 00:23:57.309
Fine. How is it at the back?

354
00:23:58.228 --> 00:24:00.312
Not planning on being there for long.

355
00:24:01.189 --> 00:24:02.606
Ten minutes to the warm-up lap.

356
00:24:02.816 --> 00:24:04.233
Ten minutes.

357
00:24:07.654 --> 00:24:08.988
Arsehole.

358
00:24:10.407 --> 00:24:13.659
Heading into
the Grand Hotel hairpin. second gear.

359
00:24:13.743 --> 00:24:14.743
Turn in hard.

360
00:24:14.828 --> 00:24:17.496
looking for late apex.
gentle with the bar.

361
00:24:19.249 --> 00:24:22.376
Heading into Portier. second gear.
clip the apex.

362
00:24:22.461 --> 00:24:26.046
light brake. stay in second.
looking for a good exit.

363
00:24:26.381 --> 00:24:28.424
Heading through the tunnel.
gradual right.

364
00:24:28.508 --> 00:24:31.469
up through third. fourth. fifth...

365
00:24:31.553 --> 00:24:33.554
ls Alexander round?

366
00:24:34.097 --> 00:24:36.682
Er. yes. he was.

367
00:24:36.766 --> 00:24:38.350
He went back to the house
to take a call.

368
00:24:38.435 --> 00:24:40.186
He'll be back shortly.

369
00:24:40.270 --> 00:24:42.438
He only wanted to show me
his pride and joy.

370
00:24:43.398 --> 00:24:46.108
Rhymes with "boy". if you ask me.

371
00:24:46.193 --> 00:24:47.985
And "toy".

372
00:24:48.069 --> 00:24:52.281
God. it's so flimsy
for something that costs so much.

373
00:24:52.365 --> 00:24:56.368
There's no comfort.
no protection. nothing.

374
00:24:56.453 --> 00:24:59.079
No. it's just a little coffin. really.

375
00:24:59.164 --> 00:25:02.208
Surrounded by high-octane fuel in here.

376
00:25:02.292 --> 00:25:05.211
Being driven round 170 miles per hour.

377
00:25:05.295 --> 00:25:08.422
To all intents and purposes.
this thing's a bomb on wheels.

378
00:25:09.591 --> 00:25:11.509
You're James. aren't you?

379
00:25:12.761 --> 00:25:14.220
Yes.

380
00:25:15.180 --> 00:25:16.931
You fit the description.

381
00:25:17.307 --> 00:25:18.724
Ls that right?

382
00:25:19.976 --> 00:25:21.936
Suzy. Friend of Alex's.

383
00:25:22.020 --> 00:25:25.147
Yeah. yeah. I know exactly.

384
00:25:26.858 --> 00:25:28.317
What was the description?

385
00:25:28.401 --> 00:25:29.902
Mostly positive.
in terms of appearance.

386
00:25:29.986 --> 00:25:32.196
Negative only in terms of character.

387
00:25:32.739 --> 00:25:34.657
I've been told to avoid you.

388
00:25:35.033 --> 00:25:36.450
By whom?

389
00:25:36.868 --> 00:25:39.703
Alexander. He says you're a bad boy.

390
00:25:39.788 --> 00:25:42.081
Alexander doesn't know
what he's talking about.

391
00:25:42.165 --> 00:25:44.500
I was. I'm not any more.

392
00:25:44.584 --> 00:25:48.128
The new me is very professional.
Early to bed. early to rise.

393
00:25:48.213 --> 00:25:49.755
- All very dull.
- Hmm.

394
00:25:49.839 --> 00:25:51.215
But according to the team.

395
00:25:51.299 --> 00:25:53.717
"The best way to
keep beating the goose-stepper."

396
00:25:54.761 --> 00:25:56.262
Is that what you were doing
when I came in?

397
00:25:56.346 --> 00:25:59.306
Yes. visualisation techniques.
memorising the circuit.

398
00:25:59.391 --> 00:26:02.059
in this case Monaco. which is up next.

399
00:26:06.898 --> 00:26:10.025
Personally. I've always been a great
believer in getting there on the day.

400
00:26:10.110 --> 00:26:12.611
putting my foot down
and playing chicken with everyone else.

401
00:26:14.906 --> 00:26:16.365
But they don't want me
doing that any more.

402
00:26:16.449 --> 00:26:20.536
They want my body like a temple
and my mind like a monk.

403
00:26:21.204 --> 00:26:24.331
And what about your soul. your heart?

404
00:26:24.416 --> 00:26:26.542
Well. they've got ideas about that. too.

405
00:26:26.626 --> 00:26:29.169
They want me to stop messing around.
settle down.

406
00:26:29.254 --> 00:26:31.463
get married
with the next nice girl I meet.

407
00:26:31.548 --> 00:26:32.965
They think it would be good for me.

408
00:26:33.425 --> 00:26:35.426
Hmm. What do you think?

409
00:26:35.802 --> 00:26:39.138
It sounds fucking awful.

410
00:26:40.223 --> 00:26:42.600
But since they're right
about most things.

411
00:26:42.892 --> 00:26:45.519
- they're probably right about that. too.
- Hmm.

412
00:26:45.604 --> 00:26:47.980
You don't fancy getting married. do you?

413
00:27:13.381 --> 00:27:14.923
Suzy.

414
00:27:15.634 --> 00:27:17.051
Bravo!

415
00:27:17.385 --> 00:27:19.303
Hey. hey. hey!

416
00:27:22.891 --> 00:27:24.808
- What's going on with him?
- Nothing. Nothing.

417
00:27:25.143 --> 00:27:26.560
Didn't want to ruin your day.

418
00:27:27.145 --> 00:27:29.563
It's... it's the Kraut.

419
00:27:29.856 --> 00:27:31.398
What about him?

420
00:27:32.275 --> 00:27:34.109
He's just been signed by Ferrari.

421
00:27:34.194 --> 00:27:37.905
You're kidding me?
Jesus. How did that happen?

422
00:27:38.198 --> 00:27:39.698
Did he buy his way in there. too?

423
00:27:39.783 --> 00:27:45.371
Well. the old man took Regazzoni back
and he insisted on it. apparently.

424
00:27:45.455 --> 00:27:47.414
He says that Niki's a genius
setting up the cars.

425
00:28:06.726 --> 00:28:08.477
It's terrible. Drives like a pig.

426
00:28:09.312 --> 00:28:11.689
- Oh. you can't say that.
- Why not?

427
00:28:12.023 --> 00:28:14.066
- It's a Ferrari!
- It's a shitbox.

428
00:28:14.567 --> 00:28:17.903
It understeers like crazy and
the weight distribution is a disaster.

429
00:28:17.987 --> 00:28:21.031
It's amazing. all these facilities
and you make a piece of crap like this.

430
00:28:22.450 --> 00:28:23.784
Uh!

431
00:28:52.522 --> 00:28:55.691
"Ferrari family."
"Our good friend Clay Regazzoni."

432
00:28:55.775 --> 00:28:59.236
You are family and friend
to the commendatore as long as you win.

433
00:28:59.320 --> 00:29:00.738
The minute you don't. ciao. ciao.

434
00:29:01.030 --> 00:29:05.159
I totally understand. It's business.
I would do the same.

435
00:29:05.285 --> 00:29:08.203
But it isn't
just business. is it? What we do.

436
00:29:08.288 --> 00:29:10.372
It's passion. love.

437
00:29:10.457 --> 00:29:13.208
Which is why we are prepared
to risk our lives for it.

438
00:29:13.293 --> 00:29:14.334
Not me.

439
00:29:14.419 --> 00:29:17.087
If I had more talent and could earn
better money with something else.

440
00:29:17.297 --> 00:29:18.881
I would.

441
00:29:18.965 --> 00:29:22.551
How do you know you will
make money here? You haven't yet.

442
00:29:22.635 --> 00:29:24.970
Not yet. but I will.

443
00:29:25.638 --> 00:29:27.514
If you can. I can.

444
00:29:31.394 --> 00:29:33.228
You know. are you ever not an asshole?

445
00:29:34.606 --> 00:29:36.565
- Why am I an asshole?
- Well...

446
00:29:36.649 --> 00:29:38.150
You know. by now
I'm both quicker than you

447
00:29:38.234 --> 00:29:40.068
and better at setting up the car.

448
00:29:40.153 --> 00:29:41.904
You can't deal with it.
so you're the asshole.

449
00:29:41.988 --> 00:29:43.155
Screw you.

450
00:29:51.080 --> 00:29:54.291
I brought you along today because
you seem like a lonely kind of guy.

451
00:29:54.375 --> 00:29:56.251
I thought if I introduced you
to some nice people.

452
00:29:56.336 --> 00:29:58.128
that could rub off on you.

453
00:29:58.213 --> 00:30:00.839
Forget it. Make your own friends.

454
00:30:00.924 --> 00:30:03.592
Come on. Clay. I'm sorry.

455
00:30:39.128 --> 00:30:40.546
Are you leaving?

456
00:30:41.673 --> 00:30:43.090
Yes.

457
00:30:43.550 --> 00:30:45.217
Can you give me a lift
to the nearest town.

458
00:30:45.301 --> 00:30:46.760
anywhere with a train station?

459
00:30:48.555 --> 00:30:51.640
Sure. Trento's half an hour's drive.

460
00:30:52.267 --> 00:30:53.308
Get in.

461
00:31:04.696 --> 00:31:08.115
# Been another blue day
without you. girl

462
00:31:09.242 --> 00:31:12.744
# Been another sad summer song

463
00:31:14.539 --> 00:31:18.500
# I been thinking about you. girl.
all night long

464
00:31:20.461 --> 00:31:21.545
What are you doing?

465
00:31:21.963 --> 00:31:23.463
You hear that noise when you accelerate?

466
00:31:23.965 --> 00:31:26.258
- No.
- Your fan belt is loose.

467
00:31:26.342 --> 00:31:28.051
My what?

468
00:31:28.136 --> 00:31:30.512
And when you brake.
your foot goes all the way down.

469
00:31:30.597 --> 00:31:32.055
which means there's air in the system.

470
00:31:32.348 --> 00:31:34.933
- Anything else?
- No.

471
00:31:35.935 --> 00:31:38.687
Apart from
the rear brakes are worn out.

472
00:31:38.980 --> 00:31:40.397
the front right tyre's a bit soft.

473
00:31:40.481 --> 00:31:42.190
which explains
why you're weaving so much.

474
00:31:42.275 --> 00:31:44.776
Hmm. How can you tell?

475
00:31:45.111 --> 00:31:47.070
- My ass.
- Sorry?

476
00:31:47.238 --> 00:31:49.114
God gave me an okay mind.

477
00:31:49.198 --> 00:31:51.909
but a really good ass.
which can feel evertyhing in a car.

478
00:31:52.243 --> 00:31:54.494
You don't know what
you're talking about. This car is fine.

479
00:31:54.579 --> 00:31:57.289
- I just had a service a week ago.
- Not a good one.

480
00:31:57.373 --> 00:32:00.000
Yes. a very good one. very expensive.

481
00:32:00.543 --> 00:32:02.628
This car is as good as new. Relax.

482
00:32:09.969 --> 00:32:11.470
Not in a hurry. are you?

483
00:32:11.554 --> 00:32:13.221
No. As long as I'm back

484
00:32:13.306 --> 00:32:14.640
in Maranello Monday morning.

485
00:32:17.060 --> 00:32:18.310
Ja.

486
00:32:18.394 --> 00:32:20.562
- Marlene.
- Niki.

487
00:33:27.296 --> 00:33:29.840
Mi scusi... Tu sei Niki Lauda?

488
00:33:30.967 --> 00:33:32.926
Yes.

489
00:33:41.853 --> 00:33:43.228
- Actually. we do. yeah.
- Okay.

490
00:33:43.312 --> 00:33:44.521
It's my honour. Niki. please.

491
00:33:44.605 --> 00:33:46.857
- Thank you.
- My car is your car.

492
00:33:46.941 --> 00:33:50.694
On one condition. though.
It's a piece of shit. It's dog shit.

493
00:33:50.778 --> 00:33:53.822
But if you drive it.
you make my life. Niki. eh?

494
00:34:06.669 --> 00:34:08.795
- Niki Lauda!
- Niki Lauda. Niki Lauda!

495
00:34:10.715 --> 00:34:13.050
Will someone please tell me
what's going on?

496
00:34:13.134 --> 00:34:14.551
Who are you? Should I know you?

497
00:34:14.635 --> 00:34:16.136
What. you don't know?

498
00:34:16.721 --> 00:34:20.640
He's Niki Lauda. Formula 1 driver.
and he just signed with Ferrari.

499
00:34:20.725 --> 00:34:22.184
- Him?
- Yes.

