00:51:24.998 --> 00:51:26.957
Oh. it's dirty politics
and dirty tricks.

743
00:51:27.000 --> 00:51:28.417
that's what's going wrong.

744
00:51:28.627 --> 00:51:31.003
So. as we approach
the halfway point

745
00:51:31.088 --> 00:51:32.838
in this year's Formula 1 season.

746
00:51:33.340 --> 00:51:36.592
Ferrari and Niki Lauda
seem clearly on top.

747
00:51:36.676 --> 00:51:39.720
and James Hunt and McLaren
are struggling.

748
00:51:39.846 --> 00:51:43.265
So. five races in.
how's it going so far?

749
00:51:43.683 --> 00:51:46.936
It's fine. Just got a little problem
with an Austrian rat

750
00:51:47.020 --> 00:51:48.604
and his team of ltalian cheats

751
00:51:48.688 --> 00:51:51.148
- who have destroyed my car.
- What are you talking about?

752
00:51:51.191 --> 00:51:53.359
I'm talking about the race in Spain
that I won.

753
00:51:53.485 --> 00:51:56.695
- Yeah. in a car which is not legal.
- Five-eighths of an inch too wide.

754
00:51:56.780 --> 00:51:59.031
You know that doesn't have
the slightest effect on speed.

755
00:51:59.157 --> 00:52:01.534
But you complained and your team
of lawyers leaned on the authorities.

756
00:52:01.660 --> 00:52:04.787
Now we've had to rebuild the car.
and it's become a monster.

757
00:52:04.871 --> 00:52:07.832
- At least it's a legal monster.
- You've had to resort to cheating.

758
00:52:08.166 --> 00:52:11.710
You're driving an illegal car
and call me the cheat? It's pathetic.

759
00:52:11.837 --> 00:52:15.047
- Rules are rules.
- Yes. and rats are rats.

760
00:52:15.132 --> 00:52:16.215
Thank you. Thank you.

761
00:52:19.511 --> 00:52:22.179
Do you really think it upsets me. James.

762
00:52:22.222 --> 00:52:25.182
calling me a rat
because I look like one?

763
00:52:25.225 --> 00:52:26.976
I don't mind it.

764
00:52:27.060 --> 00:52:28.894
Rats are ugly. sure.
and nobody likes them.

765
00:52:28.979 --> 00:52:32.690
but they're very intelligent and
they have a strong survival instinct.

766
00:52:32.732 --> 00:52:34.400
- Wonderful.
- Marlene. komm.

767
00:52:36.069 --> 00:52:37.528
No wonder she left him.

768
00:52:55.380 --> 00:52:56.881
Anyone seen Suzy?

769
00:52:58.550 --> 00:53:01.010
She's supposed to be here today.

770
00:53:01.094 --> 00:53:04.221
We. er... didn't wanna tell you
before the race.

771
00:53:05.182 --> 00:53:06.765
Tell me what?

772
00:53:12.105 --> 00:53:13.564
Jesus.

773
00:53:38.298 --> 00:53:39.798
Ls that from him?

774
00:53:40.383 --> 00:53:41.800
Yeah.

775
00:53:48.308 --> 00:53:50.476
So when did all this start?

776
00:53:51.728 --> 00:53:53.979
That weekend I went skiing.

777
00:53:56.816 --> 00:53:59.068
Why have you come here. James?

778
00:53:59.653 --> 00:54:01.070
I've come to get you back.

779
00:54:02.280 --> 00:54:04.156
You don't want me back.

780
00:54:04.282 --> 00:54:05.908
You never wanted to be married
in the first place.

781
00:54:05.992 --> 00:54:08.327
- Yes. I did.
- Oh. come on. James.

782
00:54:08.912 --> 00:54:11.413
You did it because
you hoped it might change you.

783
00:54:11.498 --> 00:54:13.165
settle you down. help with the racing.

784
00:54:13.500 --> 00:54:14.917
No. I didn't.

785
00:54:15.126 --> 00:54:17.294
And who knows?
If it had been just the drinking

786
00:54:17.337 --> 00:54:21.131
or the dope or the infidelity
or the moods.

787
00:54:21.174 --> 00:54:22.299
it might even have worked.

788
00:54:23.134 --> 00:54:24.927
- But when it's all of them...
- Yes. I know. I'm terrible.

789
00:54:25.011 --> 00:54:26.845
No. you're not terrible.

790
00:54:27.847 --> 00:54:31.016
You're just who you are
at this point in your life.

791
00:54:33.311 --> 00:54:34.979
God help anyone who wants more.

792
00:54:37.649 --> 00:54:40.859
And Richard Burton.
will he able to give you more?

793
00:54:42.362 --> 00:54:44.780
You know. he has quite
the bad boy reputation himself.

794
00:54:45.865 --> 00:54:48.534
What's important is how it feels to me.

795
00:54:48.660 --> 00:54:50.953
and it feels like he adores me.

796
00:54:57.460 --> 00:54:58.877
- James!
- New York Times!

797
00:54:58.962 --> 00:55:00.379
Are you and Suzy getting back together?

798
00:55:00.463 --> 00:55:03.382
- James. how do you feel...
- It's all very amicable.

799
00:55:03.466 --> 00:55:06.010
My wife has found herself
a new backer...

800
00:55:06.052 --> 00:55:08.554
I mean. lover. which makes her happy.

801
00:55:08.638 --> 00:55:11.181
And Mr Burton has found
a way of feeling young again.

802
00:55:11.224 --> 00:55:12.683
which makes him happy.

803
00:55:12.726 --> 00:55:15.019
Let's hope his pockets are deep.
They'll need to be.

804
00:55:15.061 --> 00:55:18.314
And I've found a way to be single
and have an ex-wife

805
00:55:18.398 --> 00:55:20.065
without it costing me a penny.

806
00:55:20.150 --> 00:55:22.318
which has got to go down
as the biggest win of my career.

807
00:55:22.402 --> 00:55:25.112
...l have a flight to catch.

808
00:56:52.909 --> 00:56:55.494
We haven't seen
this sort of intensity

809
00:56:55.537 --> 00:56:57.162
fpom James Hunt all season long.

810
00:56:57.205 --> 00:57:00.165
Reports have been coming out
of the McLaren camp all week

811
00:57:00.208 --> 00:57:03.669
that their car is now fully legal
and faster than ever.

812
00:57:13.430 --> 00:57:15.556
Never mind the bloody wets.
We're still quick.

813
00:57:19.686 --> 00:57:23.063
Hunt has really closed the gap on Lauda
as they head into Druids.

814
00:57:25.233 --> 00:57:28.026
Niki Lauda is under real pressure
fpom James Hunt

815
00:57:28.069 --> 00:57:30.737
as they go up the hill
into Druids Corner.

816
00:57:36.578 --> 00:57:38.412
And Hunt is in front of Lauda!

817
00:57:45.920 --> 00:57:47.296
So James Hunt gets the plaudits

818
00:57:47.380 --> 00:57:49.214
of the crowd. the first Briton to win

819
00:57:49.299 --> 00:57:50.924
a British Grand Prix at Brands Hatch

820
00:57:51.050 --> 00:57:52.926
since Jim Clark in 1964.

821
00:57:56.598 --> 00:57:58.557
James. at the moment
you've got a terrific edge

822
00:57:58.600 --> 00:58:01.560
over the rest of the field.
How have you achieved this advantage?

823
00:58:01.978 --> 00:58:03.562
Big balls.

824
00:58:03.646 --> 00:58:05.105
Would you...

825
00:58:05.273 --> 00:58:08.233
Following an inquiry
into the disqualification

826
00:58:08.318 --> 00:58:10.736
of driver James Hunt
from the Spanish Grand Prix.

827
00:58:10.820 --> 00:58:12.237
it has been decided

828
00:58:12.322 --> 00:58:14.239
- to overturn this disqualification...
- Yes!

829
00:58:14.324 --> 00:58:17.743
...and to restore his victory
and reinstate his points.

830
00:58:23.958 --> 00:58:25.417
James! James!

831
00:58:25.460 --> 00:58:27.294
James. a few weeks ago
you were out of the running

832
00:58:27.420 --> 00:58:29.254
for the season completely.
and now you're right back in it.

833
00:58:29.339 --> 00:58:32.257
- What's changed?
- Well. it's a combination of factors -

834
00:58:32.300 --> 00:58:34.426
not all of which I'm prepared
to discuss here -

835
00:58:34.469 --> 00:58:38.805
but justice being done
re the disqualification in Spain helps.

836
00:58:38.932 --> 00:58:41.350
and having my car
back at its best again.

837
00:58:58.326 --> 00:58:59.952
James! James!

838
01:01:29.477 --> 01:01:31.687
Welcome to the legendary Nürburgring.

839
01:01:32.438 --> 01:01:34.272
This is a 14.2-mile track.

840
01:01:34.774 --> 01:01:38.110
complete with 185 corners and bends.

841
01:02:37.086 --> 01:02:38.920
Welcome to the Nürburgring.

842
01:02:39.005 --> 01:02:41.590
the most dangepous circuit
on the season calendar.

843
01:02:41.924 --> 01:02:44.718
In Formula 1 it is known
as the Graveyard.

844
01:02:44.844 --> 01:02:46.553
The weather conditions
are far from ideal.

845
01:02:46.679 --> 01:02:48.221
and latest reports indicate

846
01:02:48.347 --> 01:02:50.015
there is no relief in sight.

847
01:02:54.854 --> 01:02:59.858
Gentlemen. Well. gentlemen.
please be quiet.

848
01:02:59.901 --> 01:03:02.068
Thank you. Niki Lauda.

849
01:03:02.278 --> 01:03:03.779
Thank you.

850
01:03:04.697 --> 01:03:07.908
I called this meeting because.
as all you drivers know.

851
01:03:08.034 --> 01:03:10.202
the Nürburgring is the most stupid.
barbaric. outdated

852
01:03:10.244 --> 01:03:11.703
and dangerous track in the world.

853
01:03:11.746 --> 01:03:14.039
You've all seen the rain
that has been falling today.

854
01:03:14.081 --> 01:03:17.709
Now. those of you with experience know
the ring needs perfect conditions

855
01:03:17.794 --> 01:03:20.420
to be even remotely acceptable
in terms of risk.

856
01:03:20.546 --> 01:03:22.923
And today. with the rain.
it's anything but perfect.

857
01:03:23.049 --> 01:03:26.134
so I called this meeting to
take a vote to cancel the race.

858
01:03:26.219 --> 01:03:28.261
Cancel the race?

859
01:03:28.387 --> 01:03:30.388
There would be no change
to the situation

860
01:03:30.431 --> 01:03:31.890
as far as points is concerned.

861
01:03:31.933 --> 01:03:34.559
- The race would simply be cancelled.
- This is bullshit.

862
01:03:34.644 --> 01:03:36.895
If the race is cancelled.
none of us get our race fees.

863
01:03:36.979 --> 01:03:41.316
That's true. you leave without your fee.
but you might leave with your life.

864
01:03:41.400 --> 01:03:45.654
It also means that you would
effectively win the championship.

865
01:03:46.072 --> 01:03:48.615
So. I can see why
this suits you just fine.

866
01:03:48.991 --> 01:03:51.576
Why? There would be
no points for me either.

867
01:03:51.911 --> 01:03:54.246
No. but there would be one race less

868
01:03:54.288 --> 01:03:56.623
where I. or anyone else here.
could catch you.

869
01:03:56.707 --> 01:03:59.000
James is right. This is just tactics.

870
01:03:59.085 --> 01:04:01.753
Maybe he's just frightened.

871
01:04:03.297 --> 01:04:04.798
Which asshole said this?

872
01:04:10.596 --> 01:04:13.640
Yes. of course I'm frightened.
and so are you.

873
01:04:15.852 --> 01:04:19.521
I accept. every time I get in my car.
there is 20 per cent chance I could die.

874
01:04:19.605 --> 01:04:21.147
and I can live with it.

875
01:04:21.274 --> 01:04:23.275
but not one per cent more.

876
01:04:23.317 --> 01:04:25.652
And today. with the rain.
the risk is more.

877
01:04:25.778 --> 01:04:28.488
I suppose that all depends
on how good you are in the rain.

878
01:04:28.948 --> 01:04:30.782
I have the track record here.

879
01:04:30.825 --> 01:04:33.702
I am the only person in history
to do the ring in under seven minutes.

880
01:04:33.786 --> 01:04:36.496
So. actually. it's to my advantage
to race here today.

881
01:04:38.124 --> 01:04:40.500
Because I'm quicker than all of you.

882
01:04:41.544 --> 01:04:44.838
- Come on.
- Fine. Then let's race.

883
01:04:46.465 --> 01:04:48.842
- Come on. Niki. let's race.
- Gentlemen. please.

884
01:04:48.968 --> 01:04:50.635
Why are we here. Niki? Come on.

885
01:04:56.893 --> 01:04:59.519
Well. all those in favour
of cancelling the race.

886
01:05:09.739 --> 01:05:11.489
All those in favour of racing.

887
01:05:17.872 --> 01:05:19.331
Gentlemen. the race is on.

888
01:05:26.172 --> 01:05:28.214
- Ridiculous.
- What a waste of time.

889
01:05:29.717 --> 01:05:32.552
You know. Niki. every now and then
it helps if people like you.

890
01:05:48.903 --> 01:05:51.029
In places
the track is still dangerously wet.

891
01:05:51.072 --> 01:05:52.530
but following a drivers' meeting.

892
01:05:52.615 --> 01:05:54.115
a decision has finally been taken.

893
01:05:55.451 --> 01:05:57.118
The race is going ahead.

894
01:06:01.374 --> 01:06:02.540
Niki!

895
01:06:02.583 --> 01:06:04.376
One minute to go.

896
01:06:13.886 --> 01:06:17.055
Jochen's going on slicks.
You wanna change?

897
01:06:17.098 --> 01:06:19.557
- Is Niki gonna change?
- No.

898
01:06:19.642 --> 01:06:21.726
Then we stay on wets. too.

899
01:06:29.568 --> 01:06:31.319
- Niki. okay?
- I'm good.

900
01:06:33.781 --> 01:06:36.282
All right. fire her up.

901
01:06:49.630 --> 01:06:52.257
This season's fight for
the Formula 1 World Championship

902
01:06:52.299 --> 01:06:55.927
has so far been the story of two men.

903
01:06:55.970 --> 01:06:59.597
Thus far. it's been going
pretty much the way of Niki Lauda.

904
01:06:59.640 --> 01:07:02.308
But James Hunt
has qualified fastest here.

905
01:07:02.435 --> 01:07:05.437
He is on pole position
for the German Grand Prioo

906
01:07:05.521 --> 01:07:08.606
with Niki Lauda alongside
in the blood-red Ferrari.

907
01:07:10.026 --> 01:07:11.443
It's a long race.

908
01:07:11.527 --> 01:07:14.154
If the track starts to dry out.

909
01:07:14.280 --> 01:07:17.115
the wet-weather tyres
will no longer be as quick.

910
01:07:38.554 --> 01:07:40.555
Niki Lauda
and James Hunt. side by side

911
01:07:40.639 --> 01:07:43.808
on the front row of the grid.
go away absolutely as one.

912
01:07:57.990 --> 01:08:00.200
Lauda very aggressive on Hunt there.

913
01:08:00.326 --> 01:08:02.327
forcing the McLaren onto the grass.

914
01:08:06.665 --> 01:08:08.083
Lauda has the lead at the moment.

915
01:08:08.167 --> 01:08:10.502
Lauda leads into the first corner.

916
01:08:10.711 --> 01:08:12.670
Hunt is in second place.

917
01:08:17.343 --> 01:08:19.928
Mass storming past Hunt!

918
01:08:20.012 --> 01:08:22.680
He made the right choice
to go with the dry-weather tyres.

919
01:08:24.183 --> 01:08:26.017
Mass passing Lauda now!

920
01:08:26.102 --> 01:08:30.021
Jochen Mass. in the number 12 McLaren.
takes the lead!

921
01:08:30.189 --> 01:08:31.898
Jochen Mass the clear leader.

922
01:08:32.024 --> 01:08:34.067
with everybody else making the decision

923
01:08:34.193 --> 01:08:36.277
to change tyres
afterjust one lap of this race.

924
01:08:36.362 --> 01:08:38.571
He's coming in! Come on. let's go!

925
01:08:46.705 --> 01:08:50.750
See? I told you to go on slicks.
You should have taken my advice.

926
01:08:50.876 --> 01:08:52.627
Fuck off. Where's Niki?

927
01:08:52.711 --> 01:08:55.380
Behind you.
He made the same mistake.

928
01:09:08.144 --> 01:09:09.894
Come on!

929
01:09:12.439 --> 01:09:14.232
Come on! What's going on?

930
01:09:15.776 --> 01:09:19.070
The tyre-changing frenzy has caused
a huge reshuffling of the pack.

931
01:09:19.113 --> 01:09:22.073
- with Jochen Mass in the lead now.
- You're clear. Go!

932
01:09:22.658 --> 01:09:23.741
Quick!

933
01:09:25.244 --> 01:09:26.995
Lauda urging his mechanics to hurry.

934
01:09:27.079 --> 01:09:28.246
Quicker. quicker. quicker!

935
01:09:29.999 --> 01:09:32.083
It's a disaster! Come on!

936
01:09:43.637 --> 01:09:45.180
What's going on. you assholes?

937
01:10:08.954 --> 01:10:11.122
This race has gone wrong for him so far.

938
01:10:11.207 --> 01:10:14.626
His championship rival. James Hunt.
is a long way up the poad.

939
01:10:25.512 --> 01:10:26.971
Lauda passing car after car.

940
01:10:27.014 --> 01:10:30.475
He's just going past
Mario Andretti's Lotus there.

941
01:11:17.189 --> 01:11:19.190
Niki!

942
01:11:24.196 --> 01:11:26.281
Get me out! Help me!

943
01:11:26.865 --> 01:11:29.200
We have an accident
on the course. Red flags are out.

944
01:11:29.702 --> 01:11:33.538
Several cars are involved. Looks like
it might be one of the Ferraris.

945
01:11:40.713 --> 01:11:43.089
- Come this way.
- Come on. come on!

946
01:11:55.311 --> 01:11:56.728
Keep trying.

947
01:12:04.403 --> 01:12:05.945
- Come this way.
- Okay.

948
01:13:44.336 --> 01:13:47.755
The flood. which swept
down Big Thompson Canyon in Colorado.

949
01:13:47.840 --> 01:13:49.507
was the worst since records began.

950
01:13:49.550 --> 01:13:52.093
In Formula 1 today.
victory celebrations were muted

951
01:13:52.177 --> 01:13:55.930
after a horrific accident involving
world champion Niki Lauda.

952
01:13:56.014 --> 01:13:57.932
Due to safety concerns before the race.

953
01:13:58.016 --> 01:14:00.351
the Austrian had said
he would not take part.

954
01:14:00.394 --> 01:14:01.894
but in the end he did.

955
01:14:03.272 --> 01:14:05.565
He was making up for lost time
when he went off the track.

956
01:14:05.691 --> 01:14:08.025
puncturing the Ferrari's fuel tank.

957
01:14:08.444 --> 01:14:10.736
Brett Lunger was unable to
avoid the flaming wreck.

958
01:14:10.863 --> 01:14:13.781
but was unhurt and joined with
the other drivers to rescue Lauda.

959
01:14:13.866 --> 01:14:16.742
who was taken to Mannheim Hospital
with severe burns.

960
01:14:16.869 --> 01:14:20.538
the incident reminding us again
of the dangers of Formula 1.

961
01:14:20.622 --> 01:14:22.623
Niki Lauda was trapped
for almost a minute

962
01:14:22.708 --> 01:14:25.376
in a searing inferno
of 800-plus degrees.

963
01:14:34.219 --> 01:14:36.387
- Do we have any change this morning?
- No...

964
01:14:36.472 --> 01:14:38.389
Frau Lauda. Frau Lauda?

965
01:19:12.164 --> 01:19:14.039
- Morning. chaps.
- Hey. here's the man.

966
01:19:14.249 --> 01:19:15.875
Looking good.

967
01:19:19.129 --> 01:19:21.922
- What's going on?
- Jesus. It's Niki.

968
01:19:22.007 --> 01:19:24.049
- What about him?
- He's here.

969
01:19:24.342 --> 01:19:25.885
- What?
- He's racing.

970
01:19:41.234 --> 01:19:42.860
Niki.

971
01:19:49.534 --> 01:19:51.035
It's that bad. huh?

972
01:19:52.370 --> 01:19:53.746
No.

973
01:19:54.623 --> 01:19:57.541
In hospital I asked them straight.
no bullshit.

974
01:19:57.626 --> 01:19:59.460
how bad my appearance would be.

975
01:20:00.712 --> 01:20:03.088
They said with time it would be fine.

976
01:20:03.965 --> 01:20:05.549
But it won't.

977
01:20:06.468 --> 01:20:09.303
I can tell. seeing your reaction.

978
01:20:10.263 --> 01:20:13.265
I will spend the rest of my life
with a face that frightens people.

979
01:20:17.395 --> 01:20:21.148
You know. Niki. I tried to write you
a letter at the time. to apologise.

980
01:20:22.818 --> 01:20:25.277
The drivers' meeting in Germany.
before the race.

981
01:20:25.403 --> 01:20:27.905
- I swayed the room.
- Yes. you did.

982
01:20:28.114 --> 01:20:30.324
That race should never have gone ahead.

983
01:20:31.076 --> 01:20:32.660
No. it shouldn't.

984
01:20:33.119 --> 01:20:36.747
So. in many ways. I feel responsible
for what happened. and...

985
01:20:36.832 --> 01:20:38.415
You were.

986
01:20:40.085 --> 01:20:41.794
But. trust me...

987
01:20:42.963 --> 01:20:47.007
watching you win those races
while I was fighting for my life...

988
01:20:49.302 --> 01:20:52.513
...you were equally responsible
for getting me back in the car.

989
01:21:20.292 --> 01:21:22.960
- How are you feeling. Niki?
- Fine.

990
01:21:23.378 --> 01:21:26.964
Niki. can you confirm to us exactly
which procedures you've had

991
01:21:27.007 --> 01:21:29.008
and the expectations for your recovery?

992
01:21:29.551 --> 01:21:31.010
Sure.

993
01:21:31.177 --> 01:21:32.970
I had a skin graft operation.

994
01:21:33.013 --> 01:21:35.306
where they put half my right thigh
in my face.

995
01:21:37.517 --> 01:21:42.313
Now. it doesn't look too good.
but one unexpected advantage is

996
01:21:42.355 --> 01:21:44.648
it's impossible to perspire
through a skin graft.

997
01:21:44.733 --> 01:21:48.068
so sweat will never run into my eyes
again. which is good for a driver.

998
01:21:50.363 --> 01:21:51.989
When they heard about your condition.

999
01:21:52.032 --> 01:21:55.492
Ferrari immediately hired
a replacement driver. Carlos Reutemann.

1000
01:21:56.161 --> 01:22:00.164
Yeah. before even reaching the hospital.

1001
01:22:00.206 --> 01:22:02.249
Ls Reutemann driving today. too?

1002
01:22:02.667 --> 01:22:05.669
Yes. and keen to make an impression.

1003
01:22:05.879 --> 01:22:09.840
So. let's see where Mr Reutemann
finishes and where I finish today.

1004
01:22:11.384 --> 01:22:14.094
James Hunt and McLaren have
caught up a lot while you were away.

1005
01:22:14.721 --> 01:22:16.180
Yes.

1006
01:22:16.848 --> 01:22:19.767
So is there a question now.
or are you just trying to piss me off?

1007
01:22:23.104 --> 01:22:24.855
You still think you can win?

1008
01:22:25.273 --> 01:22:27.024
Yes. of course.

1009
01:22:27.067 --> 01:22:29.068
I have the better car.

1010
01:22:29.194 --> 01:22:31.695
And possibly I'm the better driver.

1011
01:22:31.863 --> 01:22:34.281
But he's a clever guy.
and he's used his time well

1012
01:22:34.366 --> 01:22:38.410
while I was lying half-dead in hospital
to win some points.

1013
01:22:40.372 --> 01:22:43.040
And what did your wife say
when she saw your face?

1014
01:22:49.255 --> 01:22:52.716
She said. "Sweetie.
you don't need a face to drive.

1015
01:22:52.801 --> 01:22:54.927
"You just need a right foot."

1016
01:22:55.220 --> 01:22:57.596
I'm being serious.

1017
01:22:57.806 --> 01:23:02.267
Do you really think your marriage can
survive with the way you look now?

1018
01:23:04.938 --> 01:23:06.939
And I'm being serious. too.

1019
01:23:07.941 --> 01:23:10.901
Fuck you. Press conference over.

1020
01:23:16.116 --> 01:23:17.908
- That was hairy.
- Well. you got noticed. Clive.

1021
01:23:17.951 --> 01:23:19.243
I'll tell you that.

1022
01:23:19.327 --> 01:23:20.911
I thought it went well.
to be honest.

1023
01:23:20.996 --> 01:23:22.746
They don't like it
when it's not going their way.

1024
01:23:22.789 --> 01:23:24.498
- Clive.
- That's the game.

1025
01:23:24.582 --> 01:23:26.834
- See you.
- See you later.

1026
01:23:26.918 --> 01:23:28.794
- James. are you all right?
- Good. yeah.

1027
01:23:28.920 --> 01:23:30.587
Listen. I think
I've got something for you

1028
01:23:30.672 --> 01:23:32.423
on that last question. about Niki.

1029
01:23:32.465 --> 01:23:35.092
- You heard about that?
- I did.

1030
01:23:36.302 --> 01:23:38.053
James.

1031
01:23:44.269 --> 01:23:46.854
Please. James...

1032
01:23:47.856 --> 01:23:50.774
Now go home to your wife
and ask her how you look.

1033
01:23:53.194 --> 01:23:54.611
Prick.

1034
01:24:11.463 --> 01:24:16.341
So Niki Lauda. just 42 days after
his near-fatal accident at Nürburgring.

1035
01:24:16.468 --> 01:24:17.968
will race here today at Monza

1036
01:24:18.053 --> 01:24:21.805
against all medical advice
and no doubt in incredible pain.

1037
01:24:54.506 --> 01:24:56.173
...Niki Lauda!

1038
01:25:04.891 --> 01:25:07.267
Photographers.
please clear the grid.

1039
01:25:07.519 --> 01:25:09.686
Niki. it's time.

1040
01:25:11.189 --> 01:25:12.689
Okay?

1041
01:25:19.364 --> 01:25:20.739
Please clear the grid.

1042
01:25:23.409 --> 01:25:25.536
One minute to go.

1043
01:26:11.332 --> 01:26:14.168
The returning Niki Lauda
seems overwhelmed.

1044
01:26:14.252 --> 01:26:16.670
He's being overtaken by car after car.

1045
01:26:26.472 --> 01:26:29.600
Lauda's off line.
He runs wide onto the grass.

1046
01:26:34.439 --> 01:26:36.106
He wrestles it back onto the track.

1047
01:26:36.316 --> 01:26:39.109
but that was a bad moment for Niki.

1048
01:26:42.989 --> 01:26:45.199
Niki Lauda's the reigning
world champion.

1049
01:26:45.283 --> 01:26:48.493
but maybe in his current state
he's a danger out there.

1050
01:26:48.620 --> 01:26:51.455
to himself and to the rest of the field.

1051
01:26:53.458 --> 01:26:57.336
And Stuck has collided
with Mario Andretti's Lotus!

1052
01:26:57.462 --> 01:27:00.631
Niki's boxed in. He's got nowhere to go.

1053
01:27:15.063 --> 01:27:18.649
Niki Lauda is actually
making a move. He's on Brambilla's tail.

1054
01:27:21.903 --> 01:27:24.571
He pulls out of the slipstream
to overtake.

1055
01:27:25.323 --> 01:27:27.658
Lauda's starting to find the form

1056
01:27:27.742 --> 01:27:29.701
that. early in this race.
we believed he'd lost.

1057
01:27:36.167 --> 01:27:40.254
Lauda's now lapping faster than
Reutemann and closing the gap ahead.

1058
01:27:44.175 --> 01:27:46.718
Lauda closing on Carlos Reutemann.

1059
01:27:46.844 --> 01:27:50.013
the man called in to be his replacement
in the Ferrari team.

1060
01:27:59.023 --> 01:28:00.857
And there's James Hunt's McLaren.

1061
01:28:00.942 --> 01:28:03.402
smoking stationary
by the side of the poad.

1062
01:28:07.031 --> 01:28:10.117
This is bad news for Hunt's
championship hopes.

1063
01:28:14.539 --> 01:28:15.914
It's Ronnie Peterson

1064
01:28:16.040 --> 01:28:18.417
who comes home the winner here at Monza.

1065
01:28:18.584 --> 01:28:21.461
But all eyes are on the man
who finishes a brilliant fourth.

1066
01:28:22.422 --> 01:28:24.548
Niki Lauda!

1067
01:29:05.423 --> 01:29:07.758
What a race. what a man.
what a season.

1068
01:29:07.842 --> 01:29:10.010
With a fourth-place finish
and three priceless points.

1069
01:29:10.094 --> 01:29:12.095
it means that Niki Lauda
is a major step closer

1070
01:29:12.138 --> 01:29:14.306
to retaining the World Championship.

1071
01:30:13.491 --> 01:30:16.993
So. the long. gruelling
and incredibly dramatic season

1072
01:30:17.036 --> 01:30:19.413
comes down to this final race in Japan

1073
01:30:19.497 --> 01:30:21.998
in the shadow of Mount Fuji.

1074
01:30:22.083 --> 01:30:23.500
Niki Lauda goes into

1075
01:30:23.543 --> 01:30:25.001
this deciding race at Fuji

1076
01:30:25.086 --> 01:30:27.254
just three points ahead of James Hunt.

1077
01:30:27.338 --> 01:30:31.591
Hunt knowing he must beat the Austrian
fair and square to take the title.

1078
01:30:33.177 --> 01:30:36.680
James. do you think
you can cope with the pressure?

1079
01:30:36.722 --> 01:30:40.225
Well. I've never really understood
what that means. I love my job.

1080
01:30:40.351 --> 01:30:42.394
I love competing. I love racing.

1081
01:30:42.603 --> 01:30:44.438
Maybe you should ask Niki.

1082
01:30:44.522 --> 01:30:46.857
He's the World Champion.
He's got evertyhing to lose.

1083
01:30:46.899 --> 01:30:49.192
Mr Lauda.
are you feeling pressure?

1084
01:30:49.277 --> 01:30:51.736
Do I look like I'm feeling pressure?

1085
01:30:53.781 --> 01:30:57.909
I am World Champion. and on the verge
to become World Champion again.

1086
01:30:58.035 --> 01:31:00.036
Hunt now has the opportunity to win.

1087
01:31:00.121 --> 01:31:02.205
but it's not so easy
to become a champion.

1088
01:31:02.290 --> 01:31:05.417
You have to really believe it
to make it possible.

1089
01:31:05.543 --> 01:31:07.586
James. is there anything
you'd like to add?

1090
01:31:07.712 --> 01:31:11.631
If Niki is being tricky and getting
a kicky out of playing mind games...

1091
01:31:11.716 --> 01:31:14.092
...then fine. l'm flattered.

1092
01:31:14.218 --> 01:31:17.762
But the fact is. momentum is with me.
I've never felt better.

1093
01:31:17.889 --> 01:31:20.432
And I fully expect the next
press conference we will have

1094
01:31:20.558 --> 01:31:22.726
will be with me as World Champion.

1095
01:31:24.562 --> 01:31:26.980
How will you cope
with the weather. bad conditions?

1096
01:31:27.064 --> 01:31:30.567
Intermittent heavy rain
has been forecast here at Fuji today.

1097
01:31:30.651 --> 01:31:34.112
along with strong winds
and occasional fog

1098
01:31:34.238 --> 01:31:36.114
rolling in from the mountain.

1099
01:31:37.909 --> 01:31:40.577
And so. with today's
Japanese Grand Prix to come.

1100
01:31:40.620 --> 01:31:42.412
Lauda's lead a mere three points.

1101
01:31:42.497 --> 01:31:44.164
What a way to finish the season.

1102
01:31:44.749 --> 01:31:46.249
Hunt or Lauda?

1103
01:31:46.334 --> 01:31:49.336
Well. the final chapter will unfold when
we bring you extended coverage...

1104
01:31:49.420 --> 01:31:52.464
They've got to cancel the race.
It's lethal out there.

1105
01:31:52.548 --> 01:31:54.674
The race is going ahead.

1106
01:31:54.759 --> 01:31:56.593
Television rights have been sold
all around the world.

1107
01:31:56.677 --> 01:31:59.304
The showdown between you and Niki
is all anyone wants to see.

1108
01:31:59.388 --> 01:32:02.807
With heavy rain
continuing to fall here at Fuji.

1109
01:32:02.892 --> 01:32:04.976
a decision has finally been made.

1110
01:32:05.061 --> 01:32:08.980
The 1976 Japanese Grand Prix
will go ahead.

1111
01:32:09.065 --> 01:32:11.775
All drivers
to your cars. please.

1112
01:32:36.384 --> 01:32:37.801
Five minutes to go.

1113
01:33:21.012 --> 01:33:22.429
- All right?
- All right.

1114
01:33:22.513 --> 01:33:24.848
- Hold still.
- What the hell are you doing?

1115
01:33:24.932 --> 01:33:26.641
To let the condensation out.

1116
01:33:26.726 --> 01:33:29.436
- It'll also let the water in.
- Not if you're leading.

1117
01:33:29.520 --> 01:33:31.896
Trust me.
this race is all about the start.

1118
01:33:33.816 --> 01:33:36.359
- Need a hand here?
- Yeah. hold it. Teddy.

1119
01:33:50.833 --> 01:33:52.459
Okay. start the bastard.

1120
01:33:55.463 --> 01:33:57.130
Good luck. kid.

1121
01:33:58.507 --> 01:33:59.924
Good luck. James.

1122
01:34:39.465 --> 01:34:41.466
Thirty seconds to go.

1123
01:35:00.903 --> 01:35:03.071
Electric tension here at Fuji.

1124
01:35:03.155 --> 01:35:08.201
80.000 bedraggled race fans and
the racing grudge match of the decade.

1125
01:35:08.285 --> 01:35:10.412
And there's Mario Andretti
in pole position.

1126
01:35:10.496 --> 01:35:12.497
James Hunt alongside him.

1127
01:35:14.625 --> 01:35:16.543
On Row 2 of the grid.

1128
01:35:16.627 --> 01:35:18.503
there is Niki Lauda.

1129
01:35:18.587 --> 01:35:21.047
and on Row 3 of the grid.
Jody Scheckter from South Africa

1130
01:35:21.132 --> 01:35:22.549
in the six-wheel Tyrrell.

1131
01:35:22.633 --> 01:35:24.718
Behind him.
the rest of the 25-car field.

1132
01:35:42.570 --> 01:35:46.573
There's the flag. and finally
the Japanese Grand Prix is underway!

1133
01:35:58.794 --> 01:36:01.963
In these conditions.
it must be almost impossible to drive

1134
01:36:02.047 --> 01:36:04.048
a 450-horsepower car.

1135
01:36:31.202 --> 01:36:34.204
And it's Andretti who has the lead.
but Hunt is attacking.

1136
01:36:34.288 --> 01:36:37.248
Hunt's going pound
the outside of Andretti.

1137
01:36:37.333 --> 01:36:38.875
Niki Lauda following him thpough.

1138
01:36:38.959 --> 01:36:41.711
Hunt leads into the first right-hander.

1139
01:37:24.797 --> 01:37:26.506
Hunt comes thpough
to complete his first lap.

1140
01:37:26.590 --> 01:37:28.007
leading the field.

1141
01:37:28.092 --> 01:37:30.218
At least he has clear vision
in fpont of him.

1142
01:37:30.302 --> 01:37:32.470
Niki Lauda. behind him.
eating his spray.

1143
01:37:51.949 --> 01:37:53.366
Lauda is slowing.

1144
01:37:53.450 --> 01:37:56.327
Niki Lauda is bringing
the Ferrari number one into the pit.

1145
01:37:58.080 --> 01:38:01.291
Some sort of problem. we can't
imagine what. so early in the race.

1146
01:38:07.590 --> 01:38:11.050
What's wrong with the car?
What's wrong with the car?

1147
01:38:12.219 --> 01:38:13.928
Niki. what's wrong with the car?

1148
01:38:14.263 --> 01:38:16.347
Nothing. Car's perfect.

1149
01:38:20.769 --> 01:38:23.104
- What are you doing?
- I'm stopping.

1150
01:38:23.188 --> 01:38:25.356
His mechanics
are asking what the ppoblem is.

1151
01:38:25.441 --> 01:38:27.775
But wait!
Niki Lauda's getting out of the car!

1152
01:38:27.860 --> 01:38:29.485
This is sensational!

1153
01:38:29.570 --> 01:38:32.488
The reigning World Champion.
Niki Lauda. is out of this race.

1154
01:38:33.407 --> 01:38:35.074
It's too dangerous.

1155
01:38:35.159 --> 01:38:38.369
Niki. you want me to say there was
a problem with the car. for the media?

1156
01:38:39.663 --> 01:38:41.164
No.

1157
01:38:41.540 --> 01:38:42.957
Tell them the truth.

1158
01:38:43.834 --> 01:38:45.418
Now. what is happening?

1159
01:38:45.502 --> 01:38:49.422
They're talking to the team manager.
Lauda explaining something.

1160
01:39:04.980 --> 01:39:08.274
With Lauda out. James Hunt
knows he has to finish this race

1161
01:39:08.359 --> 01:39:12.111
in third place or higher
to be World Champion.

1162
01:39:12.196 --> 01:39:14.864
But the job's not done yet
for James Hunt.

1163
01:39:14.949 --> 01:39:19.577
In these dreadful conditions.
he still has to go the distance.

1164
01:39:20.663 --> 01:39:22.538
Fifteen laps to go here at Fuji.

1165
01:39:22.623 --> 01:39:24.707
James Hunt or Niki Lauda?

1166
01:39:24.792 --> 01:39:27.877
This extraordinary season
is not over yet.

1167
01:39:27.962 --> 01:39:31.381
In this treacherous final round.
can James Hunt hang on?

1168
01:39:31.924 --> 01:39:33.758
And the scoreboard tells a story.

1169
01:39:33.842 --> 01:39:36.636
Lap 58. Hunt in the lead.

1170
01:39:38.639 --> 01:39:40.473
Oh. God. his tyres. they're blistering.

1171
01:39:42.101 --> 01:39:43.893
Brambilla very close behind now.

1172
01:39:43.978 --> 01:39:45.937
closing on him all the time now.

1173
01:39:46.021 --> 01:39:49.190
And he's trying to drive
inside James Hunt.

1174
01:39:49.274 --> 01:39:51.818
Hunt cuts acposs the orange March nose.

1175
01:39:51.902 --> 01:39:54.195
Hunt's not having that at all.
And he's spinning.

1176
01:39:54.279 --> 01:39:57.448
He missed Hunt there. but almost
took James Hunt out of the race

1177
01:39:57.533 --> 01:39:59.867
and out of the world championship.

1178
01:39:59.952 --> 01:40:02.662
Now we find Mario Andretti
closing on James Hunt.

1179
01:40:07.251 --> 01:40:09.210
Mario Andretti's going past Hunt!

1180
01:40:09.670 --> 01:40:12.672
Hunt is slowing. James Hunt
seems to have a ppoblem.

1181
01:40:18.512 --> 01:40:20.263
Despite these wet conditions.

1182
01:40:20.347 --> 01:40:22.098
these wet-weather tyres
do wear extremely fast.

1183
01:40:22.182 --> 01:40:24.308
Hunt's tyres. they've gone.

1184
01:40:24.560 --> 01:40:28.229
Hunt nursing his car
back to the pit stop.

1185
01:40:30.232 --> 01:40:32.275
That back marker's going past Hunt.

1186
01:40:44.705 --> 01:40:47.415
Look at that left fpont tyre...
Right fpont tyre. sorry.

1187
01:40:47.499 --> 01:40:50.626
No tread on it at all.
And the other one is flat.

1188
01:40:50.794 --> 01:40:52.920
Let's go! Let's go!

1189
01:40:57.468 --> 01:40:59.886
Okay? When did you break
your gear lever?

1190
01:40:59.970 --> 01:41:01.554
Nine or ten laps ago.

1191
01:41:01.638 --> 01:41:04.098
- Alastair. we need to lift it.
- Come on!

1192
01:41:04.183 --> 01:41:05.892
- At the front.
- Let's go.

1193
01:41:05.976 --> 01:41:09.145
Regazzoni's Ferrari
and Jacques Lafitte in the Ligier

1194
01:41:09.229 --> 01:41:10.897
have gone ahead.

1195
01:41:10.981 --> 01:41:12.607
Come on. hurry!

1196
01:41:12.691 --> 01:41:15.735
You did it.
You're going to be World Champion!

1197
01:41:15.819 --> 01:41:17.236
Not yet.

1198
01:41:17.321 --> 01:41:21.074
A few laps ago. James Hunt
was looking like champion elect.

1199
01:41:21.158 --> 01:41:23.534
Now it looks as though
it's all gone wpong for him.

1200
01:41:24.953 --> 01:41:26.370
- James.
- Come on!

1201
01:41:26.455 --> 01:41:27.872
- Listen.
- What?

1202
01:41:27.956 --> 01:41:30.208
Just go easy out there.

1203
01:41:30.292 --> 01:41:34.253
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying look after yourself.

1204
01:41:34.338 --> 01:41:36.214
We want you back in one piece.

1205
01:41:36.298 --> 01:41:39.634
You're too far back. There's
too many drivers in front of you.

1206
01:41:39.718 --> 01:41:43.721
- There's always next year.
- So that's it? It's over?

1207
01:41:44.139 --> 01:41:45.598
Clear!

1208
01:41:45.682 --> 01:41:47.183
James.

1209
01:41:48.894 --> 01:41:50.812
- Clear!
- Fuck it!

1210
01:41:54.733 --> 01:41:57.944
James Hunt rejoins the race
in sixth position.

1211
01:41:58.028 --> 01:42:01.906
There are four laps left to go.
Surely no way back for the Brit now.

1212
01:42:21.802 --> 01:42:23.052
Concentrate. Superstar.

1213
01:42:23.220 --> 01:42:24.929
Just brings it back under contpol.

1214
01:42:25.055 --> 01:42:26.222
Sliding the McLaren

1215
01:42:26.306 --> 01:42:27.557
on the very edge there.

1216
01:42:29.476 --> 01:42:30.768
Hunt's M23

1217
01:42:30.894 --> 01:42:32.436
twitching this way and that
under braking.

1218
01:42:32.563 --> 01:42:33.938
And he almost loses it right there.

1219
01:42:34.064 --> 01:42:36.274
Hunt on the tail
of Jacques Lafitte in the blue Ligier.

1220
01:42:44.741 --> 01:42:46.159
Oh. don't do it. James.

1221
01:42:49.580 --> 01:42:51.164
He's inches away
fpom the pit wall.

1222
01:42:51.248 --> 01:42:53.040
He's inches away fpom the Ligier.

1223
01:43:02.092 --> 01:43:04.468
James Hunt has made up another place.

1224
01:43:04.553 --> 01:43:05.553
but it's not enough.

1225
01:43:05.637 --> 01:43:06.888
and this race is running out.

1226
01:43:15.939 --> 01:43:17.899
And Watson has spun.
Watson has spun.

1227
01:43:22.571 --> 01:43:25.323
Hunt manages to weave his way
between that back marker

1228
01:43:25.407 --> 01:43:27.408
and the stationary Penske.

1229
01:43:27.492 --> 01:43:29.493
He's catching Regazzoni

1230
01:43:29.578 --> 01:43:31.204
but. in these conditions.
it's one thing to catch up.

1231
01:43:31.288 --> 01:43:33.497
it's quite another to overtake.

1232
01:43:36.877 --> 01:43:41.005
He's alongside Clay Regazzoni.
This could be the world championship.

1233
01:43:49.431 --> 01:43:50.973
He's got him!

1234
01:44:06.240 --> 01:44:08.324
Hunt cposses the line.

1235
01:44:08.408 --> 01:44:11.994
Now. he needed to finish third to score
enough points to be World Champion.

1236
01:44:12.079 --> 01:44:16.582
and in the confusion here. we're being
told that he may have finished fifth.

1237
01:44:16.667 --> 01:44:18.793
He finished fifth?

1238
01:44:18.877 --> 01:44:21.671
Our lap charts
show Hunt in third place.

1239
01:44:21.755 --> 01:44:23.673
Well. if the scoreboard's right.

1240
01:44:23.757 --> 01:44:26.259
it means he's just missed out
on the championship.

1241
01:44:26.343 --> 01:44:30.012
Crushing defeat for Hunt
after such a hepoic drive.

1242
01:44:33.976 --> 01:44:36.477
I can see the race stewards conferring.

1243
01:44:36.561 --> 01:44:38.187
examining the official lap charts.

1244
01:44:38.272 --> 01:44:40.690
We're just going to have to wait
for their verdict here.

1245
01:44:58.333 --> 01:44:59.875
Let's get you out of there. buddy.

1246
01:44:59.960 --> 01:45:02.044
I'm sorry. Teddy. I'm sorry.
I thought I could make up the ground.

1247
01:45:02.129 --> 01:45:04.213
Sorry? What are you talking about?
You did it.

1248
01:45:04.298 --> 01:45:07.049
- Did what?
- Jesus. You crazy bastard.

1249
01:45:07.134 --> 01:45:10.303
You came third. You got the points.
You're champion of the world!

1250
01:45:10.846 --> 01:45:14.098
James Hunt
is now officially confirmed

1251
01:45:14.182 --> 01:45:16.225
as finishing third here in Japan.

1252
01:45:16.893 --> 01:45:20.521
and that means
he is champion of the world.

1253
01:45:21.982 --> 01:45:27.278
Our new World Champion.
James Hunt. by just one single point.

1254
01:45:32.492 --> 01:45:33.951
Did we really win?

1255
01:45:38.040 --> 01:45:40.291
World bloody Champion!

1256
01:45:49.092 --> 01:45:50.968
Tell us. James.
what are you going to do now?

1257
01:45:51.053 --> 01:45:53.179
I shall be getting drunk.

1258
01:45:53.722 --> 01:45:56.432
It's wonderful.
an absolute dream...

1259
01:46:43.438 --> 01:46:45.439
And our special guest.

1260
01:46:45.524 --> 01:46:47.358
Formula 1 champion James Hunt.

1261
01:47:10.757 --> 01:47:12.842
Wait. Come on.

1262
01:47:16.012 --> 01:47:17.471
There's no better motor oil

1263
01:47:17.556 --> 01:47:19.140
than Havoline.

1264
01:47:29.693 --> 01:47:31.610
Yes. me. too.
Where are we going?

1265
01:47:31.695 --> 01:47:33.154
Anywhere I want to go.

1266
01:47:33.238 --> 01:47:35.489
And I don't have to hijack it. either.

1267
01:47:35.574 --> 01:47:37.199
As long as I pay for it.

1268
01:47:37.284 --> 01:47:39.618
I'm starving.
Let's get some food.

1269
01:47:50.714 --> 01:47:52.423
- Where are we going?
- You lot go ahead.

1270
01:47:52.507 --> 01:47:54.467
I won't be a minute.

1271
01:48:00.390 --> 01:48:02.016
Good to see you.

1272
01:48:06.062 --> 01:48:08.481
I heard you were spending
more and more time in one of these.

1273
01:48:08.899 --> 01:48:10.858
- Do you fly?
- No.

1274
01:48:11.234 --> 01:48:12.735
I don't think they'd insure me.

1275
01:48:12.861 --> 01:48:14.737
You should try.
It's good for discipline.

1276
01:48:14.905 --> 01:48:17.406
You have to stay within the rules.
stick to regulations.

1277
01:48:17.532 --> 01:48:20.075
suppress the ego.
It helps with the racing.

1278
01:48:20.202 --> 01:48:23.162
And there I was thinking
you were about to wax lyrical

1279
01:48:23.246 --> 01:48:24.830
about the romance of flight.

1280
01:48:25.207 --> 01:48:26.749
No. that's all bullshit.

1281
01:48:27.918 --> 01:48:29.376
So. what brings you here?

1282
01:48:30.504 --> 01:48:33.005
A friend's wedding.
At least I think it was a wedding.

1283
01:48:33.089 --> 01:48:35.925
Might have been a birthday or something.
It's all a bit of a blur.

1284
01:48:36.009 --> 01:48:37.259
How about you? Have you been at Fiorano?

1285
01:48:37.302 --> 01:48:38.469
Pre-season testing.

1286
01:48:38.595 --> 01:48:40.513
- You're relentless.
- Thank you.

1287
01:48:40.597 --> 01:48:42.765
I'm not sure that was meant
as a compliment.

1288
01:48:42.849 --> 01:48:45.100
When do you start testing? Next week?

1289
01:48:45.143 --> 01:48:47.102
No. What. are you nuts?

1290
01:48:47.187 --> 01:48:48.938
I didn't just win
the biggest thing of my life

1291
01:48:48.980 --> 01:48:50.439
so I could get right back to work.

1292
01:48:51.775 --> 01:48:54.443
Why? You have to.

1293
01:48:54.778 --> 01:48:58.113
To prove to all the people who will
always say you just won it because...

1294
01:48:58.198 --> 01:49:01.617
Because of what?
Because of your accident?

1295
01:49:03.119 --> 01:49:05.162
Niki. is that other people.
or is that you?

1296
01:49:05.789 --> 01:49:08.874
I won. okay? On the all-important day.
when it came down to it.

1297
01:49:08.959 --> 01:49:11.794
we raced on equal terms.
equally good cars.

1298
01:49:11.878 --> 01:49:14.046
And I put my life on the line.
and I saw it through.

1299
01:49:14.130 --> 01:49:16.173
- And you call that winning?
- Yes.

1300
01:49:16.299 --> 01:49:18.342
The risks were totally unacceptable.

1301
01:49:18.885 --> 01:49:21.345
You were prepared to die.
To me. that's losing.

1302
01:49:21.471 --> 01:49:23.055
Yes. I was. I admit it.

1303
01:49:23.139 --> 01:49:25.975
I was prepared to die
to beat you that day.

1304
01:49:26.017 --> 01:49:28.978
And that's the effect you have on me.
You'd pushed me that far.

1305
01:49:29.062 --> 01:49:30.479
And it felt great.

1306
01:49:31.398 --> 01:49:33.732
I mean. hell.
isn't that what we're in this for?

1307
01:49:33.817 --> 01:49:37.152
To stare death in the face
and to cheat it?

1308
01:49:37.529 --> 01:49:41.323
Come on. there's nobility in that.
It's... it's like being knights.

1309
01:49:42.325 --> 01:49:44.076
You English. you're such assholes.

1310
01:49:45.036 --> 01:49:46.495
You know my position.

1311
01:49:46.746 --> 01:49:48.163
Twenty per cent risk.

1312
01:49:48.248 --> 01:49:52.001
No. no. no. Niki. don't bring the
percentages into this. Don't be a pro.

1313
01:49:52.043 --> 01:49:54.670
The minute you do that.
you kill what's good about this.

1314
01:49:55.005 --> 01:49:56.755
You kill the sport.

1315
01:49:59.884 --> 01:50:01.510
James!

1316
01:50:01.845 --> 01:50:03.679
- James!
- Come on!

1317
01:50:06.683 --> 01:50:08.058
I've got to go.

1318
01:50:09.561 --> 01:50:11.520
Careful in this thing.

1319
01:50:12.564 --> 01:50:14.023
James.

1320
01:50:19.279 --> 01:50:23.032
You know. in hospital. the toughest part
of my treatment was the vacuum.

1321
01:50:23.366 --> 01:50:26.285
Pumping the shit out of my lungs.
It was hell.

1322
01:50:27.370 --> 01:50:29.288
And while doing it.
I was watching television.

1323
01:50:29.873 --> 01:50:32.625
- You winning all my points.
- Your points?

1324
01:50:32.709 --> 01:50:34.918
"That bastard Hunt." I would say.
"I hate that guy."

1325
01:50:35.462 --> 01:50:37.546
And then one day
the doctor came and said.

1326
01:50:37.631 --> 01:50:39.923
"Mr Lauda.
may I offer a piece of advice?

1327
01:50:40.050 --> 01:50:43.719
"Stop thinking of it as a curse to
have been given an enemy in life.

1328
01:50:43.803 --> 01:50:45.971
"It can be a blessing. too.

1329
01:50:46.056 --> 01:50:48.807
"A wise man gets more from his enemies
than a fool from his friends."

1330
01:50:49.434 --> 01:50:51.727
And you know what? He was right.

1331
01:50:54.314 --> 01:50:58.067
Look at us. We were both
a pair of kids when we met.

1332
01:50:58.109 --> 01:50:59.902
Hot-headed jerks in Formula 3.

1333
01:50:59.944 --> 01:51:01.779
...Disowned by our families.

1334
01:51:01.905 --> 01:51:03.280
Headed nowhere.

1335
01:51:04.407 --> 01:51:06.659
And now we're both
champions of the world.

1336
01:51:06.743 --> 01:51:08.160
It was not bad. huh?

1337
01:51:09.245 --> 01:51:11.163
No. it's not bad.

1338
01:51:11.247 --> 01:51:14.792
So. don't let me down now.
I need you busting my balls.

1339
01:51:15.251 --> 01:51:18.003
- Get back to work.
- I will. Niki. I will.

1340
01:51:18.755 --> 01:51:20.798
But I intend to enjoy myself first.

1341
01:51:21.174 --> 01:51:23.467
Some of life needs to be for pleasure.

1342
01:51:23.593 --> 01:51:26.929
What's the point of having
a million cups and medals and planes

1343
01:51:27.013 --> 01:51:29.139
if you don't have any fun?

1344
01:51:29.974 --> 01:51:31.684
How is that winning?

1345
01:51:32.769 --> 01:51:35.479
- James!
- We're gonna leave without you!

1346
01:51:35.980 --> 01:51:37.439
James!

1347
01:51:41.277 --> 01:51:42.695
I'll see you on race day. champ.

1348
01:51:44.447 --> 01:51:46.615
You will... champ.

1349
01:51:49.119 --> 01:51:50.869
You look good. Niki.

1350
01:51:51.454 --> 01:51:54.331
The only guy to have his face burnt off
and it be an improvement.

1351
01:52:01.172 --> 01:52:03.215
Of course.
he didn't listen to me.

1352
01:52:03.299 --> 01:52:04.717
For James.

1353
01:52:04.801 --> 01:52:06.969
one world title was enough.

1354
01:52:07.011 --> 01:52:08.470
He had ppoved

1355
01:52:08.513 --> 01:52:11.807
what he needed to ppove. to himself

1356
01:52:11.891 --> 01:52:14.143
and anyone who doubted him.

1357
01:52:15.019 --> 01:52:16.895
And two years later he retired.

1358
01:52:17.147 --> 01:52:20.816
When I saw him next in London
seven years later.

1359
01:52:20.900 --> 01:52:23.026
me as champion again.

1360
01:52:23.153 --> 01:52:25.028
him as broadcaster.

1361
01:52:25.113 --> 01:52:29.533
he was barefoot
on a bicycle with a flat tyre.

1362
01:52:29.659 --> 01:52:32.494
Still living each day like his last.

1363
01:52:34.247 --> 01:52:35.706
When I heard he'd died.

1364
01:52:35.832 --> 01:52:38.208
aged 45. of a heart attack.

1365
01:52:38.334 --> 01:52:39.835
I wasn't surprised.

1366
01:52:40.837 --> 01:52:42.713
I was just sad.

1367
01:52:44.090 --> 01:52:45.924
People always think of us as rivals.

1368
01:52:46.009 --> 01:52:49.595
but he was among the very few I liked.

1369
01:52:50.930 --> 01:52:53.891
and even fewer that I respected.

1370
01:52:57.020 --> 01:52:59.772
He remains the only person I envied.

1371
02:02:38.809 --> 02:02:40.810
Subtitling: Deluxe Digital Studios
